&lt;p&gt;ETCH is a startup commercializing a radically new and efficient decarbonization technology for the simultaneous greenhouse gas-free production of hydrogen and solid carbon from natural gas.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Electrical Engineer position at ETCH, INC will be focused on development, testing, verification, and improvement of electric systems and instrumentation.&amp;nbsp; Primary duties are designing the electrical architecture of a scaled up heating system, ensuring the optimal performance, efficiency, and safety of heating systems, and driving continuous improvements and innovations in design.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Other duties include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Author equipment and instrumentation hardware descriptions including requirements, functional specifications, and system architecture descriptions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop troubleshooting plans and calculation and analysis documents to support design reviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Author factory acceptance test procedures and develop program for instrument checking, calibration, and testing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design systems in compliance with regulatory requirements such as the National Electric Code&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and manage electrical construction documentation and coordinate drawings with other disciplines and outside firms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate in the technical oversight and direction of external design teams (engineering firms) and internal design teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate and assist in the assessment of customer needs and capture requirements and functions of the electrical design for process systems.&lt;/li&gt;
