&lt;li&gt;Author I&amp;amp;C system hardware descriptions including requirements, functional specifications, and I&amp;amp;C system architecture descriptions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop troubleshooting plans and calculation and analysis documents to support design reviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Author factory acceptance test procedures and develop program for instrument checking, calibration, and testing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate in the technical oversight and direction of external design teams (engineering firms) and internal design teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate and assist in the assessment of customer needs and capture requirements and functions of the I&amp;amp;C design for process systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recommend process system design modifications and improvements to improve quality of products and/or procedures from a construction, commissioning, operations, maintenance, and/or decommissioning perspective.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead reviews and presentations for internal and external design reviews regarding I&amp;amp;C process systems design.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in Process Hazards Analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design systems in compliance with regulatory requirements such as the National Electric Code&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implementation of hardware and software following company policies and procedures such as Management of Change and Lock Out/Tag Out.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible work schedule including third shift&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
