&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Thermal Mechanical Engineer – Job Description&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Baltimore, MD&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Full-time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ETCH is a startup commercializing a radically new and efficient decarbonization technology for the simultaneous greenhouse gas-free production of hydrogen and solid carbon from natural gas.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Primary duties include leading the design and development of advanced reactor systems and supporting infrastructure. This role will be central to scaling from pilot to commercial systems, with a strong emphasis on reactor bundles, high-temperature design, and balance-of-plant (BOP) integration. Focus will be on design, improving performance and efficiency, and safety of the processes all while driving continuous improvements and innovations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Other duties include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reactor &amp;amp; Core System Design&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and optimize annulus reactor bundles, including thermal uniformity, flow distribution, and mechanical integrity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop detailed mechanical designs for pilot reactor modifications and scale-up to 5 MTPD (metric tons per day) reactor systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform thermal and structural calculations for high-temperature operation (≥1000°C environments)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate materials of construction considering creep, thermal expansion, and chemical compatibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Structural &amp;amp; Mechanical Systems&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design structural supports for reactor systems, accounting for thermal expansion, vibration, and load conditions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure mechanical robustness and maintainability of reactor assemblies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop expansion joints, supports, and interfaces between hot and cold sections&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Balance of Plant (BOP) &amp;amp; Layout&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead mechanical design and layout for balance-of-plant systems, including:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Heat exchangers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Piping systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Valves and flow control&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gas handling systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop plant layout and equipment arrangement for pilot and commercial facilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure proper integration between reactor core and BOP systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Engineering Analysis &amp;amp; Optimization&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct thermal modeling (CFD/FEA preferred) and heat transfer analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform stress analysis and lifecycle evaluation of critical components&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support optimization of system efficiency, uptime, and reliability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Execution &amp;amp; Scale-Up&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support transition from pilot to commercial-scale systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with fabrication teams, vendors, and operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in installation, commissioning, and troubleshooting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
